cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the geometric properties of knot and link diagrams and their drawings in the plane. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper studies the properties of 4-regular plane multigraphs and their drawings. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the topology and combinatorics of knots and links. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the concept of relaxations of Lombardi drawings, which could be related to network visualization. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the algorithmic aspects of drawing knots and links in the plane.
